Interface LazyLocaleMessageProvider

    public interface LazyLocaleMessageProvider

    Multiverse 2 LazyMessageProvider

    This interface describes a Multiverse-MessageProvider that only loads locales when they're needed.

      • loadLocale

        void loadLocale​(java.util.Locale locale)
         throws NoSuchLocalizationException,
                LocalizationLoadingException

        Loads a localization for a specified Locale.

        If that localization is already loaded, this method will reload it.
        Parameters:
        locale - The desired Locale.
        Throws:
        LocalizationLoadingException - When an error occurs while trying to load the specified localization.
        NoSuchLocalizationException - When no localization was found for the desired locale.
